15/03/2011
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal will deliver its verdict against Croatian generals Ante Gotovina, Ivan Cermak and Mladen Markac on April 15th, the court announced on Monday (March 14th). 
The three were indicted on war crimes stemming from 1995's Operation Storm, and accused of participating in a joint criminal enterprise to ethnically cleanse Serbs from the Krajina region. 
(Hina, HRT, tportal.hr, Radio Free Europe - 14/03/11)
